		The Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, Cairo University is one of the oldest veterinary colleges in the Middle East and Africa. Its roots go back to more than 170 years ago. A large number of veterinarians from Egypt, Arab and African countries have been graduated since then. The Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, Cairo University has suitable, always improving, facilities for teaching sciences of veterinary medicine. It also employs a satisfactory body of staff members who obtained their postgraduate degrees from different international veterinary schools in different disciplines of veterinary science. Based on the history and contemporary qualifications of the Faculty of Veterinary Medicine, Cairo University, the faculty aims to enforce its programme to be able to obtain accreditation on both national and international levels.
The Department of Pathology is one of the oldest departments at the level of Veterinary Medicine, where it was created with the establishment of the first school of Veterinary Medicine.
