<p>Department Mission:</p>
<p> Pathology department aims to train undergraduate and graduate students to recognize the pathological changes that occur in the tissues and organs of the animal body and through the use of a microscope. The department also aims to train students to dissect the dead animals to reach an accurate diagnosis and the cause of the deaths. The department also conducted scientific research to interact with the community to assist in the diagnosis of diseases affecting livestock.</P>
	<p>
Pathology department is equipped by a dissection room supervised by the academic staff members and, we provide necropsy service for all kinds of animals brought either from the faculty hospital or by the owners with full P.M report (Macro. and Micro.) done by the academic staff members from Sunday to Thursday (from 10 am to 01 pm). The department has a histological unit concerned with tissue processing, staining and microscopic examination of tissue samples.
